{"article_id":"33AuI5QkFasaUm2p","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"WASHINGTON -","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"Emotions are high","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"as Brett Kavanaugh 's Supreme Court confirmation vote approaches ,","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"and Maine Republican Sen. Susan Collins has found herself at the center of a fevered effort","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"to block President Donald Trump 's second nominee to the high court .","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"Kavanaugh 's opponents have identified Collins , along with Alaska Sen. Lisa Murkowski , as Senate Republicans","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"who could potentially vote against Trump 's Supreme Court pick .","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"The opposition is largely driven by abortion-rights activists ' fear","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"that Kavanaugh could be the justice","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"whose vote overturns the landmark 1973 Roe v. Wade decision .","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"Collins , in particular , seems to have become the focus of the stop-Kavanaugh movement .","depth":5},{"id":11,"text":"The senator 's office has reported receiving threatening calls and letters as well as more than 3,000 wire coat hangers in grim a reference to the unsafe , illegal abortions","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"that","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"abortion-rights defenders say","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"would follow the end of Roe v. Wade .","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"And a controversial crowdfunding campaign has raised more than $ 1.1 million","depth":6},{"id":16,"text":"to give to a future Collins opponent","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"if she votes to confirm Kavanaugh .","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"Sen. Collins :","depth":5},{"id":19,"text":"Supreme Court nominee Brett Kavanaugh considers Roe v. Wade 'settled law '","depth":5},{"id":20,"text":"More :","depth":5},{"id":21,"text":"Abortion-rights activists send hangers to Sen. Collins ,","depth":6},{"id":22,"text":"hoping to influence her vote on court","depth":6},{"id":23,"text":"Collins told The Wall Street Journal","depth":7},{"id":24,"text":"that she finds `` the out-of-state voicemails","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"being left on the answering machines of my state offices ''","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"to be `` incredibly offensive . ''","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"`` In one case","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"- and we are going to turn this over to the police ,","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"but unfortunately , of course , the person didn ' t leave a name or number -","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"but they actually threatened to rape one of my young female staffers , ''","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"Collins told the Journal .","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"One incensed voter left a voicemail for Collins ,","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"which her office shared with ,","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"in which he repeatedly screamed insults","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"while wondering","depth":12},{"id":36,"text":"how Collins could accept Kavanaugh 's statement","depth":12},{"id":37,"text":"that he considers Roe v. Wade to be `` settled law ''","depth":12},{"id":38,"text":"when he was `` handpicked by the Federalist Society","depth":13},{"id":39,"text":"specifically to overturn '' that decision .","depth":13},{"id":40,"text":"`` You will go down in history as the most naive person ever","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"to be in Congress you ( expletive ) ,","depth":13},{"id":42,"text":"( expletive ) ,","depth":13},{"id":43,"text":"feckless , naive woman ! ''","depth":12},{"id":44,"text":"the caller yelled .","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"`` If you care at all about women 's choice ,","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"vote no Kavanaugh .","depth":12},{"id":47,"text":"Do n't be a dumb b -- -h , ''","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"another male caller said .","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"A letter","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"sent to Collins ' office","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"warned","depth":7},{"id":52,"text":"that","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"if she votes to confirm Kavanaugh","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"`` EVERY waitress","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"who serves you","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"is going to spit in your food ,","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"and that 's","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"if you 're lucky you","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"( expletive ) . ''","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"Collins said","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"she considers the crowdfunding campaign","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"raising money for whoever might challenge her in 2020","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"to be an attempt at bribery .","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"More than 40,000 donors have contributed to the effort ,","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"which pledges","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"they wo n't be charged","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"if Collins votes against Kavanaugh .","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"`` I consider this quid pro quo fundraising to be the equivalent of an attempt","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"to bribe me","depth":12},{"id":70,"text":"to vote against Judge Kavanaugh , ''","depth":12},{"id":71,"text":"she told the conservative site Newsmax .","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"She also told the Journal","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"that two lawyers told her","depth":12},{"id":74,"text":"the campaign violated federal bribery law","depth":12},{"id":75,"text":"and a third said","depth":12},{"id":76,"text":"it was extortion .","depth":12},{"id":77,"text":"Jordan Libowitz , a spokesman for the Citizens for Ethics and Responsibilities , told The Washington Post","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"that","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"while the fundraising campaign may seem `` icky ,","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"'' it `` does n't rise to the level of bribery","depth":11},{"id":81,"text":"because there 's no agreement . ''","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"`` It ' s just the way","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"money and politics tend to work these days , ''","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"Libowitz told the Post .","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"Crowdpac spokesman T.J. Adams-Falconer told Vox ,","depth":9},{"id":86,"text":"`` The notion","depth":13},{"id":87,"text":"that this grassroots activism amounts to bribery","depth":13},{"id":88,"text":"is ridiculous and insulting to the more than 40,000 Mainers and other Americans","depth":14},{"id":89,"text":"who are making their voice heard through this campaign . '' `` Your swing vote could decide","depth":14},{"id":90,"text":"whether a rubber stamp for Trump ' s anti-healthcare , anti-woman , anti-labor agenda gets confirmed to the Supreme Court","depth":13},{"id":91,"text":"- costing millions of Americans their healthcare , their right","depth":13},{"id":92,"text":"to choose ,","depth":13},{"id":93,"text":"and their lives , ''","depth":12},{"id":94,"text":"reads a statement on the Crowdpac page ,","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"which was set up by the Maine People 's Alliance , Mainers for Accountable Leadership and activist Ady Barkan .","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"`` If you fail to stand up for the people of Maine and for Americans across the country ,","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"every dollar","depth":13},{"id":98,"text":"donated to this campaign","depth":13},{"id":99,"text":"will go to your eventual Democratic opponent in 2020 , ''","depth":12},{"id":100,"text":"it reads .","depth":10},{"id":101,"text":"`` We will get you out of office . ''","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"A tweet from Sen. Orin Hatch 's office said ,","depth":8},{"id":103,"text":"`` Every Democrat should be condemning these antics in Maine -","depth":9},{"id":104,"text":"attempting to bribe Senator Collins to vote against Judge Kavanaugh","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"and threatening sexual violence against staffers","depth":12},{"id":106,"text":"if she votes for him","depth":12},{"id":107,"text":"is absolutely disgusting . ''","depth":10},{"id":108,"text":"Collins and her staff have said","depth":8},{"id":109,"text":"the aggressive tactics","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"to sway her vote","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"are a wasted effort .","depth":9},{"id":112,"text":"`` Bribery will not work on Senator Collins , ''","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"Collins ' spokeswoman Annie Clark told .","depth":10},{"id":114,"text":"`` Senator Collins will make up her mind","depth":11},{"id":115,"text":"based on the merits of the nomination .","depth":11},{"id":116,"text":"Threats or other attempts","depth":12},{"id":117,"text":"to bully her","depth":12},{"id":118,"text":"will not play a factor in her decision making whatsoever . '' `","depth":11},{"id":119,"text":"` I ' m going to do what I think is right , ''","depth":10},{"id":120,"text":"Collins told the Journal .","depth":10},{"id":121,"text":"`` I am going to cast my vote","depth":11},{"id":122,"text":"- as I have done on all of the other Supreme Court nominees","depth":12},{"id":123,"text":"that I ' ve been called upon to consider -","depth":12},{"id":124,"text":"based on his qualifications , his character and integrity , judicial temperament , his record , and his respect for the rule of law and fidelity to the Constitution . ''","depth":10}],"relations":[{"parent":249,"left":0,"right":248,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":248,"left":141,"right":247,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":141,"left":130,"right":140,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":130,"left":126,"right":129,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":126,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":129,"left":127,"right":128,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":127,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":128,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":140,"left":133,"right":139,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":133,"left":132,"right":10,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":132,"left":7,"right":131,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":131,"lef